FR940412-1-00005 FR940412-1-00001 PART 103_POWERS AND DUTIES OF SERVICE OFFICERS; AVAILABILITY OF SERVICE RECORDS 1. The authority citation for part 103 continues to read as follows: Authority: 5 U.S.C. 552, 552a; 8 U.S.C. 1101, 1103, 1201, 1252 note, 1252b, 1304, 1356; 31 U.S.C. 9701; E.O. 12356, 47 FR 14874, 15557, 3 CFR, 1982 Comp., p. 166; 8 CFR part 2. 2. In §103.7, paragraph (b)(1) is amended by adding, in proper numerical sequence, the following forms to the list of forms, to read as follows: §103.7 Fees. (b) *␣*␣* (1) *␣*␣* Form I&hyph;68. For application for issuance of the Canadian Border Boat Landing Permit under section 235 of the Act_$16.00. The maximum amount payable by a family (husband, wife, and any minor children under 18 years of age) shall be $32.00. * * * * * Form I&hyph;94. For issuance of Arrival/Departure Record at a land border Port-of-Entry under section 286 of the Act_$6.00. Form I&hyph;94W. For issuance of Nonimmigrant Visa Waiver Arrival/Departure Form at a land border Port-of-Entry under section 217 of the Act_$6.00. * * * * * Form I&hyph;175. For issuance of Nonresident Alien Canadian Border Crossing Card (Form I&hyph;185)&hyph;$30.00. Form I&hyph;175. For issuance of replacement Nonresident Alien Mexican Border Crossing Card (Form I&hyph;586) in lieu of one lost, stolen, or mutilated_$26.00. * * * * * Form I&hyph;444. For issuance of a Mexican Border Visitors Permit issued in conjunction with presentation of a Mexican Border Crossing Card or multiple-entry B&hyph;1/B&hyph;2 nonimmigrant visa to proceed for a period of more than 72 hours but not more than 30 days and to travel more than 25 miles from the Mexican border but within the five-state area of Arizona, California, Nevada, New Mexico, or Texas_$4.00. The maximum amount payable by a family (husband, wife, and any minor children under 18 years of age) shall be $8.00. * * * * * PART 212_DOCUMENTARY REQUIREMENTS: NONIMMIGRANTS; WAIVERS; ADMISSION OF CERTAIN INADMISSIBLE ALIENS; PAROLE 3. The authority citation for part 212 continues to read as follows: Authority: 8 U.S.C. 1101, 1102, 1103, 1182, 1184, 1225, 1226, 1228, 1252; 8 CFR part 2. 4. Section 212.6 is amended by revising paragraph (e) to read as follows: §212.6 Nonresident alien border crossing cards. * * * * * (e) Replacement. If a nonresident alien border crossing card has been lost, stolen, mutilated, or destroyed, the person to whom the card was issued may apply for a new card as provided for in this section. A fee as prescribed in §103.7(b)(1) of this chapter must be submitted at time of application for the replacement card. The holder of a Form I&hyph;185, I&hyph;186 or I&hyph;586 which is in poor condition because of improper production may be issued a new form without submitting fee or application upon surrendering the original card. * * * * *
